OL,7,FAfter Mr Brackenridge resigned, Mr Lee
OL,8,Fis believed to have tried to withdraw
OL,9,Fhis resignation, but it was accepted
OL,10,Fbefore he could.
OL,12,FThe two had been in a public spat on
OL,13,Fsocial media in the lead-up to the
OL,14,Fresignations.
OL,16,FThe argument involved Mr Lee posting
OL,17,Fmessages supposedly sent to him by Mr
OL,18,FBrackenridge and alleging he had been
OL,19,Ftreated with "legal action" because of
OL,20,Fhis social media posts.
